 Japanese representations of China—and as a study of Yosano herself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Japanese.2bisacsh1 aAkiko, Yosano, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFogel, Joshua A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFogel, Joshua.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044247240uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/yosa1231840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231506663423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231506663/original  a978-3-11-044247-2  Columbia University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagec2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK